================================================================================
Reverse-engineering provenance and the fxe source port
================================================================================

This project reverse-engineers Jane's Fighters Anthology (1998, Electronic Arts)
for the purpose of documentation and interoperability. The reverse-engineering
documentation is the primary output. The code (fx_lib, fx, fxs, fx_render,
and the fxe source port) exists to validate that documentation.

Clean-room provenance
---------------------
All code here is written or generated CLEAN-ROOM from this project's own
documentation of behaviour and from non-copyrightable facts (interface and
export signatures, structure layouts, virtual addresses, and algorithms
described in prose). It is NOT a transcription of the original program's
compiled or decompiled expression. Decompiler output is used only to establish
facts; it is never copied into this repository.

fxe — source-port model, requires original content
---------------------------------------------------
fxe is a clean-room, modern C++ re-implementation ("source port") of the game
executable, generated from this project's symbol database and subsystem
documentation. fxe ships NO game data: no textures, audio, missions, models,
text, or other assets from Jane's Fighters Anthology. It is inert without
content that the user must supply from their own, legally obtained copy of the
game (the same model used by ScummVM, OpenMW, and similar projects).

No game assets — of any format — are committed to this repository.

